classes.description: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.See CSS classes API below for more details.
classes.description_zh: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.See CSS classes API below for more details.

color.description: The color of the component. It supports both default and custom theme colors, which can be added as shown in the palette customization guide.
color.description_zh: The color of the component. It supports both default and custom theme colors, which can be added as shown in the palette customization guide.

enableColorOnDark.description: If true, the color prop is applied in dark mode.
enableColorOnDark.description_zh: If true, the color prop is applied in dark mode.

position.description: The positioning type. The behavior of the different options is described in the MDN web docs. Note: sticky is not universally supported and will fall back to static when unavailable.
position.description_zh: The positioning type. The behavior of the different options is described in the MDN web docs. Note: sticky is not universally supported and will fall back to static when unavailable.

sx.description: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles.See the `sx` page for more details.
sx.description_zh: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles.See the `sx` page for more details.
